  "text": "The AX-CPT is a variant of the continuous performance task (CPT; [CITATION_1] , and is commonly used in cognitive control experiments [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Cognitive control is thought to be a critical component of human high-level cognition, and refers to the ability to actively maintain and use goal-directed information to regulate behavior in a task. Cognitive control is thus used to direct attention, prepare actions, and inhibit inappropriate response tendencies. Importantly for the current paper the domain of cognitive control is thought to be one in which individual differences make a large contribution to observed performance [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] .",
